<br>
The clerk is on the phone, and not the business phone mind you he's on a cell phone. Talking away like a happy little chatter box. I guess this is not the part that bothered me because you cant really control when the phone rings.<br>
<br>
The part that bothers me is - I need to pay for my items so he's chatting happily away and hasn't even said hello and ends up ringing up one of my items twice. And as the total amount doesn't add up, I say to him &quot;Seventeen fifty for a pack of gum, ten dollars in gas and a pop?&quot; Nope, sorry, this doesnt add up. He did something wrong.<br>
<br>
The clerk, instead of politely asking the person on the phone to hold on, glares at me, huffs and checks the journal tape and begins to talk in arabic to the person on the phone.<br>
<br>
Well, it doesnt take a genious to figure out that he considers me an interuption to his phone call and routine, does it? Now he's irritated me, and the half dozen people behind me in line.<br>
<br>
&quot;Excuse me. Do you think you could take five minutes out of  your busy schedule to deal with your customers and maybe put the phone down?&quot; I didn't shout, I didn't curse and I was polite.<br>
<br>
I am the owner of a cell phone but I have never, ever gone up to a counter with the cell phone in my ear between my shoulder and tried to deal with a clerk while chatting away to my friends.<br>
<br>
I think it's positively rude on both ends.<br>
<br>
How about you? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faefiend>faefiend</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/04 1:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2390.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cell phones - Rude or Right?</span><hr size=1> Cell phone or not, what he did was damn rude. His job depends on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>you</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. He's getting paid to stand there, smile, and make sure that you're getting what you pay for. You can, after all, just take your business elsewhere - there's certainly no shortage of gas stations. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kundow>Kundow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hugs a Tree</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/04 2:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2390.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cell phones - Rude or Right?</span><hr size=1> That was pretty friggin rude.  I have a cell phone myself, but never use it when around customers at work.  Actually, I positively hate the thing, but I gotta keep in touch with folks somehow.  I dont take it in restaurants or anything either.<br>
<br>
It also bugs the crap out of me when people are on the phone while driving, and are swerving everywhere, running stop lights and just generally being a dumbass. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I talk and drive every once in a while myself, but if I can manage to hold the phone, drive a manual transmission, use my turn signals, stay in my lane, and follow all traffic laws, YOU SHOULD BE ABLE TO ALSO. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I almost got hit by some dumbass in an SUV that ran a stop light long after it turned red the other day who was running off at the mouth on a cell phone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kataliaarmourax>Katalia Armourax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/04 8:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2390.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cell phones - Rude or Right?</span><hr size=1> He's being paid to do a job, not to chat to friends. Yes, it was very rude. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.imgmag.com/images/leknill/Kepic.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sulianne>Sulianne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/04 10:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2390.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.kc.rr.com/sulianne/SuliRawr.gif height=80 width=81></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cell phones - Rude or Right?</span><hr size=1> I manage a gas station.  I totally agree with you.  He shouldn't have been on the phone at all.  My company prefers employees to not chat on the phone.  There are better things to do than babble at your friends for hours, like help customers, the people that pay our paychecks in the end.<br>
<br>
So kudos to you for standing up for yourself, and saying something.  Maybe, just maybe, he'll think twice next time.  I would recommend you mention it to the manager, if you're near there again.  They don't always realize their clerks are doing A, B, or C and it never hurts to make sure someone is aware of the problem.<br>
